Don't be mad, boss!
However, in the meantime, many citizens of the Central Asian republics who wish to work in Russia recognize that they not only do not know the language of the country to which they intend to go, but also write with difficulty in their own language.
Of course, this is not so much his fault but his own misfortune: there are few Turkmens, Uzbeks, Tajiks who can afford to receive normal primary education.
